-- Grizzlies Forward Randolph May Miss Eight Weeks With Torn Knee Ligament
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2012-01-04T19:43:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-04/grizzlies-forward-randolph-may-miss-eight-weeks-with-torn-knee-ligament.html
Memphis Grizzlies forward Zach
Randolph will miss up to eight weeks after tearing a ligament in
his right knee, the National Basketball Association team said in
a statement.  Randolph, 29, is averaging 14.8 points and 7.5 rebounds for
the 2-3 Grizzlies. He was hurt in a 104-64 loss to the  Chicago
Bulls  on Jan. 1.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  